---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const updated = 'July 5, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Agent Native Engineering"
  description="What agentnativeengineering.com collects (almost nothing), what your browser stores locally, and who processes the technical data needed to serve the site."
>
  <div class="wrap" data-r="pad">
    <article class="article">
      <a class="backlink" href="/">← Home</a>
      <header style="margin:22px 0 0">
        <div class="eyebrow">// PRIVACY</div>
        <h1 class="page-h1" data-r="page-h1" style="margin-top:14px">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="page-dek" style="margin-top:10px">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </header>
      <div class="prose" style="margin-top:30px">
        <p>
          <strong>The short version.</strong> Agent Native Engineering (<a href="https://agentnativeengineering.com">agentnativeengineering.com</a>)
          is a static, open publication. It has no accounts, no sign-in, no forms, no advertising, and
          no analytics or tracking cookies. We do not collect, sell, or share your personal information.
          The only data involved is the technical information any website needs to be delivered to your
          browser, plus one small preference your own browser stores locally.
        </p>

        <h2>What we collect directly</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing. There is no login, contact form, comment system, newsletter signup, or tracking
          pixel on this site. We do not run Google Analytics or any equivalent, and we do not set
          advertising or tracking cookies.
        </p>

        <h2>What your browser stores locally</h2>
        <p>
          The audio player on the <a href="/daily-brief/">Daily Brief</a> uses your browser's
          <code>localStorage</code> to remember your playback position in an episode, so you can resume
          where you left off. This value stays on your device, is readable only by this site, and is
          never transmitted to us or anyone else. Clearing your browser storage removes it.
        </p>

        <h2>Hosting and delivery</h2>
        <p>
          The site is hosted on <a href="https://pages.github.com/">GitHub Pages</a> and served through
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/">Cloudflare</a>'s content-delivery network. To deliver
          pages and protect against abuse, these providers automatically process standard technical
          request data — such as your IP address, browser user-agent, and the URLs you request — in
          their server logs. That processing is governed by their policies, not ours:
          <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement">GitHub's Privacy Statement</a>
          and <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.
          We do not receive individually identifying analytics from them.
        </p>

        <h2>Share buttons and external links</h2>
        <p>
          Some cards include share actions (copy link, X, LinkedIn). These do nothing until you click
          them; when you do, they hand off to that service or your clipboard using its own share
          mechanism, subject to that service's privacy policy. The site also links out to primary
          sources across the web — those destinations have their own policies, and we are not
          responsible for their practices.
        </p>

        <h2>Podcast and RSS</h2>
        <p>
          Audio files and the <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a> are plain static files. Requesting them
          involves the same hosting/CDN processing described above and no additional tracking.
        </p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>
          This site is intended for a general professional audience and is not directed to children
          under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          If our practices change, we will update this page and revise the date above. Because the site
          is open source, the full history of this policy is visible in the project's git history.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy can be sent to
          <a href="mailto:admin@agentnativeengineering.com">admin@agentnativeengineering.com</a>, or
          raised through the project on GitHub at
          <a href="https://github.com/agentnativeengineering">github.com/agentnativeengineering</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>

  <Footer slot="footer" variant="slim" left={'Privacy · <span class="strong">Agent Native Engineering</span> · CC BY 4.0'} />
</Base>
